Package com.apriori.collections

New implementations and utilities to complement the Java Collections Framework.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ConcurrentSets.Builder<E,T extends Set<E>>
    Creates concurrent set objects using the builder pattern.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayBackedLinkedList<E>
    A list implementation that attempts to achieve some of the benefits of a linked list without sacrificing the overwhelming performance advantages and memory efficiency of arrays.
    ArrayUtils
    Utility methods for working with arrays that back collection implementations.
    CollectionUtils
    Utility functions for implementing standard collection interfaces without the use of AbstractCollection and its abstract sub-classes.
    ConcurrentSets
    This utility class provides concurrent set implementations that wrap normal (non-concurrent) sets to provide thread-safe access.
    ConcurrentSortedArraySet<E>
    A NavigableSet that allows concurrent access.
    ConcurrentSortedArraySet.Builder<E>
    A builder class for constructing instances of ConcurrentSortedArraySet.
    DescendingSet<E>
    A NavigableSet that is a view of another set, but in opposite (descending) order.
    SortedArraySet<E>
    An implementation of NavigableSet that is optimized for memory efficiency at the cost of slower mutations.
